sql:
SELECT * 
FROM security_alerts 
WHERE alert_status = 'open';

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name
FROM users u
JOIN security_alerts sa ON u.user_id = sa.assigned_to;

SELECT AVG(file_size) AS average_file_size
FROM file_metadata
WHERE file_type = 0;

SELECT event_id, source_file, event_type
FROM file_events
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT u.user_name
FROM users u
INNER JOIN security_alerts sa ON u.user_id = sa.assigned_to;

external_knowledge:
The term "latest file activity" refers to the most recent event in the file events log, identified by the highest `event_id`. The "person behind" signifies the user who initiated the event, identified by `user_name`.;
"Latest" in this context means the event with the greatest `event_id`.;
The information is retrieved by linking the user who performed the event with their personal details in the users table.

sql:
SELECT users.user_name
FROM users
JOIN security_alerts ON users.user_id = security_alerts.assigned_to;

SELECT file_type, file_path
FROM file_metadata
WHERE event_id = 0;

SELECT users.user_name, file_events.event_type
FROM users
JOIN file_events ON users.user_id = file_events.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "wandering souls" refers to users who are not currently assigned to security alerts;
- "dip their toes into the murky waters of security investigations" means to be assigned to investigate security alerts;
- "untainted individuals" refers to users who have not been given any security alert tasks.
